Each of the identified marine debris falls into one of the 9 classes. These 9 classes gives us an insight of the background of the type of marine debris identified, i.e it tells us the origin or the type of material , a particular identified debris is made up of. For example : If my identified waste is a soda can, then this waste falls under the metallic class.¶

Feature Description :¶

list_id : id given to the places where the debris was found¶

master_item_id : ID given to the kind of debris found (example : cigars, can bottles etc)¶

material_index : index of the class (1-9 range)¶

latitude : latitude of the place where debris was found¶

longitude : longitude of the place where debris was found¶

master_name : The type of waste identified¶

Material : Origin/material of the type of waste identified¶
